column17: [{"dateSeen":"2024-11-30T00:14:00.000Z","value":"Discover this beautifully updated Dundalk home, where charm, modern updates, and thoughtful details come together! With a new roof, siding, kitchen, and bathrooms all completed less than a year ago, this move-in-ready property offers the perfect blend of comfort and style. The home features very large bedrooms filled with natural light, and its layout ensures privacy, with all bedrooms boasting en suite bathrooms. column99: [{"date":"2015-12-05T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.706Z","rating":4.0,"text":"I used to live in Fairmount Apartments from 2013 to 2015. It was my first and last apartment in Camp Hill after I moved from Dallas. The apartment was spacious and the staff were courteous. If I had any problems, the maintenance staff would come immediately to resolve it. The thing I absolutely loved is that they are a pet-friendly community and they have a dog park! My dogs loved it there. The community is a melting pot of various ethnicities and they are generally friendly. The community was clean and spacious. The only reason I left that apartment is because I moved to another place. But, I would highly recommend Fairmount to everyone.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-apartments-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#xjcgm9p-2-unit","https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#xjcgm9p-2-unit"],"title":"Love this place!"},{"date":"2024-03-08T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.702Z","rating":1.0,"text":"Worst place to live…. Not safe for anyone or there kids.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-apartments-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#xjcgm9p-2-unit","https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#xjcgm9p-2-unit"],"title":"Sewage problems, bug problems, fire hazards"},{"date":"2021-09-01T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.705Z","rating":1.0,"text":"Before moving in it seemed like a nice complex with decent people running it. After signing however, you're nothing but a source of revenue. on day 1 i came to an apartment that surely was not cleaned. As gross as it was, I let it slide and did the dirty work as it wasn't worth the trouble. What if something needs fixed? Just forget it, maintenance requests seems to get \\"lost\\" as no one will come to take care of it and I am talking about appliances that are older than myself. I knew they weren't new but it just goes to show how little they care as soon as they have locked you into their lease. Now what about the deposit? Nope, that's also their money, they'll find a way to keep that too even if the apartment looked better than I moved in myself. I see I am not the only one with issues from living here and should have taken a hint myself, but hopefully I can help other people make a better decision than i and just stay away from this deteriorating dump.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-apartments-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#xjcgm9p-2-unit","https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#xjcgm9p-2-unit"],"title":"Don't bother"},{"date":"2022-12-29T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.703Z","rating":1.0,"text":"Been living here for a year and some change. I have been telling them about the roaches in my apartment and since I've lived here they only came once. They maintenance is lazy, the office workers are rude, and they are money greedy. It's over priced. They get one star because of the quite neighbors and no one bothers you. Other than that the place sucks and its definitely over priced.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-apartments-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#xjcgm9p-2-unit","https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#xjcgm9p-2-unit"],"title":"DON'T DO IT"},{"date":"2021-10-06T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.704Z","rating":2.0,"text":"The door to our lobby has had a broken hinge or something for awhile now. This prevents the door from closing on its own and is often left wide open. I first reached out to maintenance about the problem on 06/21 after the door had been broken for weeks. It is not 10/05 and the issue has not been fixed. Today, I reached out for the third time at least. I attached a video showing the 50+ dead lantern flies lying on the floor in the lobby along with the trash and other debris that is very really cleaned up. The lady who answered my complaint explained that they are both short staffed and are having a hard time finding the replacement part to fix the door. column99: [{"date":"2015-12-05T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.706Z","rating":4.0,"text":"I used to live in Fairmount Apartments from 2013 to 2015. It was my first and last apartment in Camp Hill after I moved from Dallas. The apartment was spacious and the staff were courteous. If I had any problems, the maintenance staff would come immediately to resolve it. The thing I absolutely loved is that they are a pet-friendly community and they have a dog park! My dogs loved it there. The community is a melting pot of various ethnicities and they are generally friendly. The community was clean and spacious. The only reason I left that apartment is because I moved to another place. But, I would highly recommend Fairmount to everyone.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#z640t7z-2-unit"],"title":"Love this place!"},{"date":"2024-03-08T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.702Z","rating":1.0,"text":"Worst place to live…. Not safe for anyone or there kids.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#z640t7z-2-unit"],"title":"Sewage problems, bug problems, fire hazards"},{"date":"2021-09-01T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.705Z","rating":1.0,"text":"Before moving in it seemed like a nice complex with decent people running it. After signing however, you're nothing but a source of revenue. on day 1 i came to an apartment that surely was not cleaned. As gross as it was, I let it slide and did the dirty work as it wasn't worth the trouble. What if something needs fixed? Just forget it, maintenance requests seems to get \\"lost\\" as no one will come to take care of it and I am talking about appliances that are older than myself. I knew they weren't new but it just goes to show how little they care as soon as they have locked you into their lease. Now what about the deposit? Nope, that's also their money, they'll find a way to keep that too even if the apartment looked better than I moved in myself. I see I am not the only one with issues from living here and should have taken a hint myself, but hopefully I can help other people make a better decision than i and just stay away from this deteriorating dump.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#z640t7z-2-unit"],"title":"Don't bother"},{"date":"2022-12-29T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.703Z","rating":1.0,"text":"Been living here for a year and some change. I have been telling them about the roaches in my apartment and since I've lived here they only came once. They maintenance is lazy, the office workers are rude, and they are money greedy. It's over priced. They get one star because of the quite neighbors and no one bothers you. Other than that the place sucks and its definitely over priced.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#z640t7z-2-unit"],"title":"DON'T DO IT"},{"date":"2021-10-06T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.704Z","rating":2.0,"text":"The door to our lobby has had a broken hinge or something for awhile now. This prevents the door from closing on its own and is often left wide open. I first reached out to maintenance about the problem on 06/21 after the door had been broken for weeks. It is not 10/05 and the issue has not been fixed. Today, I reached out for the third time at least. I attached a video showing the 50+ dead lantern flies lying on the floor in the lobby along with the trash and other debris that is very really cleaned up. The lady who answered my complaint explained that they are both short staffed and are having a hard time finding the replacement part to fix the door. This problem has persisted for upwards of five months now with no end in sight. Since the door broke, our apartment has seen a significant uptick in flies and gnats. It seems like a matter of time before the lantern flies make their way in too. This is beyond out of control and I hope that prospective tenants take this issue into account before deciding to rent from Fairmont apartments.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#z640t7z-2-unit"],"title":"Broken door has lead to bug problem, continues to be ignored after 5+ months"},{"date":"2015-08-14T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.706Z","rating":4.0,"text":"Fairmount Park is a nice clean place to live! It stays clean and landscaped nicely! It is pretty close and convenient to grocery stores, shopping, and restaurants. The downfall is the fact that the pool closed and was not reopened nor will be. I feel the rent is too expensive for what is offered even though there is washer and dryer units in the 3 bedroom apartments. Parking can be tricky for people with more than one car if you live in the 3 bedroom apartments like I do. The apartments are pretty roomy and utilities are reasonable! Once again these apartments are pretty nice to live in!","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#z640t7z-2-unit"],"title":"A nice place to live!"},{"date":"2017-07-14T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.705Z","rating":1.0,"text":"Landlord is backing a tenant who has two German Shepherds who have attacked two dogs and killed a puppy and advising them that they are not responsible. They also have constant air conditioning issues.","sourceURLs":["https://www.apartments.com/fairmount-park-camp-hill-pa/54504sq/#z640t7z-2-unit"],"title":"PLEASE BEWARE"},{"date":"2022-02-07T00:00:00.000Z","dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:55:55.704Z","rating":1.0,"text":"This place is complete garbage and they know it but don’t care once you’ve signed the lease. column17: [{"dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:56:00.000Z","value":"Enjoy the surrounding beauty of the Colorado Rockies with views down valley to the Gore Range from this highly sought after Alders Townhome that is perched at the top of the community. This home offers main level living with an open floorplan, vaulted ceilings throughout and comes fully furnished - the residence is turnkey, just bring your skis! Meticulously maintained and cared for by the original owner and never rented - although, the investment opportunity is fantastic with rental projections around $70k a year. This prime location makes it stand out from the rest and provides the perfect blend of privacy, convenience and access to all that the mountains have to offer - from hiking, biking and golf in the summer to skiing and snowboarding in the winter. Relax after a long day on the slopes and cozy up next to the fireplace or soak in the hot tub and swim in the pool at the Dakota Lodge. The front door is just steps away from a trail that meanders along a creek and eventually connects to the base of the gondola at River Run Village and the Summit County bike path. On top of the high-end finishes throughout, additional highlights include electric shades on all windows, Lutron control switches and a 2-car garage with ample space and built-in storage racks. column17: [{"dateSeen":"2022-01-23T06:08:00.000Z","value":"Welcome home to this beautifully updated Seminole residence. Light, bright and spacious - this home is ready for immediate occupancy! From the moment you enter through the beautiful lead glass door, you will be charmed by the special touches that make this house a home. Beautiful open concept kitchen with stainless steel Samsung appliances, a breakfast bar with room for additional seating, brand new soft close doors and drawers on the white shaker style cabinets. A lovely quartz countertop and deep stainless Undermount sink complete this heart of your new home. Throughout the home there are new interior doors, stately 5 inch baseboard, updated outlets and easy care tile floors.. Don’t miss the LED flush-mount recessed lights that can be programmed from soft light to daylight. Updated bathroom with new tile shower, vanity, toilet and fixtures. The interior has been newly painted with Behr Sterling paint for a decorator feel. The exterior and even the ceilings have also been freshly painted. The Florida room has brand new Windows ($5700) for the perfect home office, playroom or to simply expand your living space. Open air patio deck is the perfect place to relax and entertain with friends. Fully fenced yard for enhanced privacy and security. There is a second full bath in the garage. The garage is partially tiled making an easy conversion to an extra bedroom if needed. Brand new electrical panel. The air conditioning system was installed new in 2017 and the roof was installed is 2014. New facia and soffit‘s were just installed in 2021. No detail has been overlooked in this great home. Sqft. provided by owner includes the Florida Room. Perfectly located just minutes to the beach, shopping, grocery stores, transportation and more. column17: [{"dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:56:00.000Z","value":"Don’t miss this beautifully designed, brand-new duplex in a prime Lehigh Acres location—perfect for savvy investors or homeowners looking to live in one unit and generate rental income from the other. Each unit offers 2 bedrooms + a den, 2 bathrooms, a 1-car garage, and 1,347 sqft. of living space and 2,694 sqft. overall. From the moment you step inside, you'll appreciate the elegant tile flooring throughout, impact-resistant windows and doors, and a modern open-concept layout that maximizes natural light and livability. The sleek kitchens feature stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops, and ample cabinet space, perfect for culinary creativity. Bathrooms are finished with luxuriously tiled showers, offering a refined and stylish touch. Whether you rent out both sides or live in one and lease the other, this property offers strong income potential and a smart way to build wealth through real estate. In today’s growing rental market, opportunities like this don’t last long."}]

column17: [{"dateSeen":"2024-10-03T20:39:00.000Z","value":"Residential | 2,468 Sq Ft | R-3"},{"dateSeen":"2024-08-23T03:36:00.000Z","value":"* * * RECENT PRICE IMPROVEMENT! * * * A vacation home that pays for itself, or a primary residence. .. you decide! Welcome to your dream home in Unincorporated Seminole. .. high-and-dry and just two blocks from the renowned Pinellas Trail! This stunning property was completely updated in 2022 and is move-in ready. With 4 bedrooms, 3 full bathrooms, and 1,911 sq. ft. of living space, there's plenty of space for everyone, as the entire second floor is dedicated to one of the TWO PRIMARY EN-SUITES, providing a private retreat. As you enter the home, you'll be welcomed by a spacious, open-concept dining room and a gourmet kitchen. The kitchen features newer appliances, modern quartz countertops, and one of three sliding-glass doors that lead to the backyard and pool area. Down the hallway, you'll find a fully remodeled guest bathroom and three additional bedrooms, including the second primary en-suite, and direct entry to the pool area. Beyond the kitchen, the expansive family room offers access to the second-floor primary en-suite, while another sliding door flows seamlessly to your private outdoor oasis. Enjoy the outdoors on the large covered lanai (with beautiful, custom mural), perfect for relaxing or entertaining, while staying protected from the elements. Take a dip in the sparkling * heated * saltwater pool, complete with multi-color LED programmable lighting. The fenced yard with maintenance-free synthetic turf is ideal for hosting gatherings or unwinding in the sun. This home is equipped with OWNED SOLAR electric panels and a two-zone split A/C system (new in 2022) for maximum energy efficiency. Located in UNINCORPORATED Seminole (within the Seminole School District) and NOT in a flood zone, this property is truly a gem! Don’t miss the opportunity to make this beautiful, updated home yours! column17: [{"dateSeen":"2022-06-07T21:38:00.000Z","value":"A Secret Tropical Paradise awaits you at this fantastic 3 bedroom, 3 Bath, 2 car garage Bay Ridge home. Nestled into a large ¼ acre lot near the former Tides Golf Club, this cool & comfy home is surrounded by an incredibly landscaped Oasis featuring two stunningly serene circulating Koi ponds with rock waterfalls outlined in palms and bamboo for privacy. (You have to see the photos, we’re talking about a Koi Pond on the West side of the home that rivals something you would see at a resort or place like Sunken Gardens) The home features a wood burning fireplace in the living room, quartz countertops and breakfast bar in the kitchen, inside laundry, bonus workshop/hobby area, pavered driveway, newer roof, etc. too much to list here. The outside entertaining area is something to behold. A gazebo contained hot tub, fire pit, screened room, tropical landscaping, an arbor covered bar area, etc. (See the photos) Located in Bay Ridge, the home is close to the Seminole City Center, Seminole Rec Center, VA, Shopping, and just minutes to the beach. This is your moment! If you love the thought of relaxing in a tropical wonderland, this home is for you. Make an appointment now to view this fantastic home. Discover your own hidden gem at 11530 66th Ave in Seminole, a beautifully updated 4-bedroom, 3-bath home with a 2-car garage, tucked away on a spacious quarter-acre lot in the coveted Bay Ridge community. Whether you're looking for a personal escape or a top-tier Airbnb opportunity, this home offers endless potential including a massive side yard with room to build your dream pool. Step outside and enter a true backyard sanctuary, surrounded by lush landscaping, bamboo privacy walls and the outdoor space also includes a screened-in lounge, fire pit, hot tub under a charming gazebo, and a covered bar area perfect for entertaining. Inside, enjoy a cozy wood-burning fireplace, quartz countertops, a breakfast bar, indoor laundry room, and even a bonus flex space ideal for hobbies or storage. With a newer roof, pavered driveway, and prime location minutes from beaches, shopping, and Seminole hot spots—this one-of-a-kind home is truly unforgettable. column17: [{"dateSeen":"2024-06-28T08:08:00.000Z","value":"Exclusive Rocky Mountain Ranch land in Lake CreekTucked away in the upper West Lake Creek Valley, just 20-minutes from Edwards, is an idyllic, equine friendly alpine utopia. This two-bedroom mountain cabin takes full advantage of its immense acreage just below New York Mountain. Surrounded by BLM & ...National Forest that will never be built on, the property includes a mountainside shooting range, great for hunters to hone their skills, and a nearby trail that winds up from the cabin to a hidden overlook at the property's edge with stunning views of New York Mountain and the pastoral meadow below. At trails end, a natural open space offers the perfect elements for a star-studded campout. A simple, split rail fence encircles the well-maintained pasture with a quaint yet durable barn that provides shelter for horses or extra storage for equipment to manage the land. Completing this authentic western Colorado setting is a tranquil stream-fed pond that can be stocked for fishing in the summer and drained in the winter when it freezes.The property's 80 acres includes a two-bedroom cabin and the potential for additional build sites. The cabin's main floor great room features vaulted ceilings and towering picture windows that showcase dramatic views of the surrounding wilderness with access to the large wrap-around deck where lounging and listening to soothing sounds of West Lake Creek flowing by is a must. The well-appointed kitchen has all the conveniences with an elegant stone-topped center island that opens to the dining area/great room and offers extra seating. A versatile loft overlooks the great room and provides extra sleeping space or storage as needed. The primary bedroom has an ensuite bath and vaulted ceilings while the second bedroom has views of the lush corral. The entire lower level is a massive, oversized 2-car garage with ample space for storing all the accessories needed to explore and enjoy this secluded mountain property. 801HolyCross.com/?mls Continue reading"},{"dateSeen":"2023-07-07T00:24:00.000Z","value":"Exclusive Rocky Mountain Ranch land in Lake Creek Tucked away in the upper West Lake Creek Valley, just 20-minutes from Edwards, is an idyllic, equine friendly alpine utopia. Surrounded on 3 sides by the Holy Cross Wilderness and White River National Forest, Eagle's Nest Ranch will forever remain uncompromised by neighbors or development. The property sits at the head of Lake Creek, one of the Vail Valley's most iconic locales. Private access into hundreds of thousands of acres of public land is right out the back door. The property is traversed by 1/4 mile of West Lake Creek, offering private high mountain fishing; and the deeded property itself, with its irrigated hay meadow, is frequented by deer and elk. For the owner who demands the extreme privacy of a quiet, secluded mountain retreat but also values the benefit of being within minutes of world-class skiing, dining, shopping, nightlife, and medical care, Eagle's Nest Ranch is simply unparalleled. A potential once in a lifetime opportunity; 775 and 777 Holy Cross Drive are also for sale. All 3 properties can be purchased providing one lucky owner 160 contiguous creekside acres. All three parcels are bordered by National Forest and are zoned resource, with no HOA or Design Review Board"},{"dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:56:00.000Z","value":"Welcome to 801 Holy Cross Drive, perhaps the most private and unique property in the Vail Valley. This spectacular 80 acre parcel is surrounded on 3 sides by the White River National Forest, providing ultimate privacy and serenity while just minutes from shopping and dining, with the Mountain Resorts of Vail and Beaver Creek less than 30 minutes away. Take advantage of a multitude of outdoor activities right out your front door, including; hiking, biking, ski-touring, 4X4 off-roading and snowmobiling, fishing, hunting and more! The site consists of two adjacent 40 acre parcels, each of which has the ability to add a main home and secondary dwelling, plus additional out-buildings as needed. The property can also be subdivided into two parcels of 40 acres each. The property includes a newly remodeled existing cabin of 1,672sf with 2 bedrooms, each with views of the lush surroundings and 2 luxurious bathrooms including an ensuite primary bath complete with steam shower. The oversized two-car garage offers ample space for all of your mountain toys and vehicles. Enjoy the captivating sounds of Lake Creek running directly through the property, plus a private pond and meadow adjacent to the cabin with fire pit and horse shelter ready to go! This turnkey cabin is ready to enjoy now with endless potential build sites for a large main residence or the option to subdivide. The future owner also has the option to put in place a valuable conservation easement. Inquire for more details. Don't miss this opportunity to capture one of the Vail Valley's most iconic properties...minutes from everything yet in a world of its own!"},{"dateSeen":"2025-07-19T14:39:00.000Z","value":"Single Family Residence - Edwards, CO"},{"dateSeen":"2022-08-28T07:12:00.000Z","value":"Exclusive Rocky Mountain Ranch land in Lake Creek Tucked away in the upper West Lake Creek Valley, just 20-minutes from Edwards, is an idyllic, equine friendly alpine utopia. column17: [{"dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:56:00.000Z","value":"This unique barndominium on 5 acres offers a rare blend of functionality and modern comfort. The living area includes 2 beds, 2 full baths, kitchen, washer/dryer area. and living room/flex space. The property includes a 3,325 sq ft building with over 2,500 sq ft of garage/shop space (with fireplace) and separate RV/boat storage with 50 AMP electric service. Originally built in 2002 and renovated in 2023, updates include but not limited to new HVAC and mini split unit, hot water heater, granite, new fixtures, new paint, fencing, etc. The property has two septic systems- one for the living space and one for the shop, The separately heated shop includes 3 bays, full bathroom, new electrical, new garage door motors, 4 post snap on car lift and is insulated. Additional features include a concrete storm shelter, commercial-grade gate, cattle guard, multiple persimmon trees, water spigots throughout property, wood burning stove in shop, and an owned propane tank. Enjoy the outdoors where you will see a lot of wildlife to include geese and deer. The pond was professionally built with clay and stocked and an underground spring, cattle enclosure with lean-to with power and lighting-- all securely enclosed with newly stained privacy fencing (8 ft along the road and 6 ft around sides). Too much to list, must see! Perfect for business owners, hobbyists, or those looking for a one-of-a-kind live/work setup! Zoned AG, so bring your animals! BA Schools!"}]

column17: [{"dateSeen":"2025-07-18T23:42:00.000Z","value":"Modern Coastal Living in the Heart of Mar Vista – No Shared Walls, No HOA Fees? Seller open to offering a 2-1 rate buydown with strong offers. Enjoy the perfect blend of privacy, design, and convenience in this stunning single-family home that lives like a townhome—but with no shared walls, no HOA, and no monthly fees. With close to 3,300 square feet of open, natural light-filled living space, this home offers contemporary comfort just minutes from the beach. Set beside its architectural twin (also a detached home), this residence offers visual harmony without structural compromise. Inside, you'll find 4 spacious bedrooms—each with its own en suite bath—plus 4.5 beautifully appointed bathrooms across a versatile multi-level layout. Wide-plank oak floors, designer smart lighting, and fully retractable Fleetwood doors create seamless indoor-outdoor living throughout. The heart of the home is a chef’s dream kitchen featuring premium Thermador appliances, custom cabinetry, a massive center island, and an oversized walk-in pantry. Upstairs, the expansive primary suite includes room for a sitting area and a home office, a custom walk-in closet, and a spa-like bath with soaking tub and separate shower. Designed for modern lifestyles, the home also features a built-in dual workstation, a private guest balcony, and a flexible top-level fourth bedroom or studio space. The oversized rooftop deck offers treetop views, refreshing ocean breezes, and seasonal firework displays—your own private sky lounge. Additional highlights include drought-tolerant landscaping, eco-conscious drip irrigation, a tandem two-car garage with extra storage, and an additional driveway parking space. Located in one of Mar Vista’s most desirable neighborhoods, you’re just minutes from Marina del Rey, Venice, and walkable shops, cafe's, and local dining hotspots Blueys and Beethoven Market. Seller is open to contributing toward a 2-1 rate buy-down for qualified buyers—ask for details! Transport with car: From Schiphol airport: 18KM, 20mins drive To Amsterdam central station: 22km, 45mins drive With Bus: From Schiphol airport: Bus 342, get off at Uithoorn Busstation, then walk 1.4KM to the house, in total it takes around 40mins. To Amsterdam: The metro line to Amsterdam is under construction for 2 years, not recommended. You have to transfer 2 times and takes more than 70mins. Dear guest, We are Sue and Frank, running own business in the Netherlands. We are both open minded and hospitable. The house is welcome for guests from different countries with various culture. We enjoy meeting people, sharing knowledge, experience and tips. The house The house has two floors. On the groundfloor , there is a large living room with dining area facing to the backyard, a bright kitchen and a toilet with shower. On the 1st floor there are 4 bedrooms, 1 bathroom with shower and toilet. Bedroom 1 with a double bed (1.6m) for 2 people, Bedroom 2 with 2 single beds. Bedroom 3 with a double bed (1.6m) for 2 people. Bedroom 4 with a single bed. In the living room, there is a sofabed of 1.4meter. The house sleeps 8 guests in total. From Schiphol airport: 18KM, 20mins drive, UBER cost 35 EURO/4 passengers car To Amsterdam central station: 22km, 45mins drive, To Amsterdam Museumplein 17KM, 30mins drive 17 mins, UBER cost 55 EURO/4 passengers car With Bus: From Schiphol airport: Bus 342, get off at Uithoorn Busstation, then walk 1.4KM to the house, the whole trip takes around 40mins. To Amsterdam: The metro line to Amsterdam is under construction for 2 years, not recommended. To Amsterdam museumplein, 1st step: 1.4km walking to Uithoorn Busstaion or take bus 340/130 near the house for 2 stops and get off at Uithoorn Busstation. 2nd step: Bus 347 directly arrives at Museumplein within 50mins. And you can change tram there to arrive at Amsterdam Central Station.Therefore it takes around 70mins to Amsterdam central station from the house. If you travel with bus to Amsterdam and cities nearby, then it's better to buy the Amsterdam & Region travel ticket, it will save the travel cost. Distance to the Uithoorn busstation 1400m, riverside (300m), supermarket and restaurant with terrace next to river(300m). Looking forward to welcoming you! Sue and Frank The guests can contact me through airbnb, send me sms, or just call me. The house located in the town Uithoorn. The town locates at 20km south of Amsterdam, near the Amstel River, it's a beautiful and quiet town. It is near Amsterdam Schiphol Airport. And you can change tram there to arrive at Amsterdam Central Station.Therefore it takes around 70mins to Amsterdam central station from the house. If you travel with bus to Amsterdam and cities nearby, then it's better to buy the Amsterdam & Region travel ticket, it will save the travel cost. Distance to the busstation 1400m, riverside (300m), supermarket and resturant with terrace next to river(300m). Special remarks need to be mentioned: There is a staircase in the house as shown in the photo, to guests who have leg problems will be difficult. We have a 1.4meter sofabed in the living room, that maybe a solution for not going upstairs. The neighbourgood is very quiet with friendly neighbours, and it has one way traffic with 30km/speed limit. The house is not allowed for having parties with loud music."}]

The heart of the home is a chef's paradise, with custom cabinets, a spacious kitchen featuring a center island, and a convenient pot filler. A large walk-in pantry, custom mud bench, and expansive laundry room add to the home's practicality. Cozy up by the wood-burning fireplace in the living room, or step outside to the covered patio with a built-in outdoor kitchen, perfect for entertaining. Situated on just under a half acre, this property offers space and privacy for your family to flourish. Welcome to a life of comfort and sophistication in this exquisite new home."}]

It contains 1 bedroom and 3 bathrooms."},{"dateSeen":"2020-06-30T19:51:00.000Z","value":"6476 Andersonville Rd is a house in Waterford Twp, MI 48329. This 2,737 square foot house sits on a 0.26 acre lot and features 1 bedroom and 2.5 bathrooms. This property was built in 2001 and last sold for $142,000. Based on Redfin's Waterford Twp data, we estimate the home's value is $544,603. Comparable nearby homes include 6024 Waterfront Dr, 4343 Lotus Dr, and 6041 Waterfront. This address can also be written as 6476 Andersonville Road, Waterford Twp, Michigan 48329."},{"dateSeen":"2025-07-23T09:56:00.000Z","value":"ENJOY YOUR SANDY BEACH AND 100' OF SHORELINE ON ALL SPORTS VAN NORMAN LAKE! SET WAY BACK FROM THE ROAD, THIS SPECTACULAR LAKEFRONT HOME with New England Charm features a circular drive, wonderful wrap around Porch, first floor Owner's Suite, first floor Laundry, finished Lower-Level Walk-out, and an elevated Composite (water proof) Deck that keeps the lower Paver Patio dry. The home offers over 4,100 SF of living space. The vaulted Foyer is open to a stunning Great Room featuring a vaulted ceiling with fan/light, beautiful open rail staircase with second floor overlook, striking stone fireplace and rich hardwood flooring. From the Foyer, French glass doors open to the Library/Den furnished with beautiful bay windows, the Dining Room features hardwood flooring and a 9' door-wall leading to the deck with glass rail for uninterrupted lake views!. The Island Kitchen and Nook feature bright cabinetry with crown molding and beautiful glass display, gorgeous granite counters, ceramic backsplash, stainless steel appliances, snack-bar counter, reverse osmosis system, pantry, ceiling fan, hardwood flooring and a door-wall opening to the deck. First floor Owner's Suite includes a corner fireplace, 9' door-wall leading to the deck, walk-in closet and private Bath with luxurious jet tub, glass enclosed shower, dual sink granite vanity, and ceramic flooring. Second floor includes 3 spacious Bedrooms and large Bath with vaulted ceiling, claw tub and step-in shower. The finished walk-out includes a huge Rec Room, TV Room, Bedroom, full Bath with travertine shower and flooring, Exercise room and Workshop with utility Tub. Oversized, 3 Car Garage is finished with, drywall, paint, rear bumper, built-in storage, attic for additional storage, service door and openers. Home Includes Additional Lot #08-32-453-003."},{"dateSeen":"2020-04-09T08:10:00.000Z","value":"Nearby schools include Our Lady of the Lakes Catholic School, Schoolcraft Elementary School and Kingsley Montgomery School. The closest grocery store is Kroger. Nearby coffee shops include L. A. Cafe and Starbucks. Nearby restaurants include Sushi Land, Sportsmens Great Northern Grill and Sportsmen's."}]

column17: [{"dateSeen":"2024-07-01T16:49:00.000Z","value":"Experience unparalleled luxury living in this custom 4300 sq ft home, perfectly situated to capture breathtaking views of Cedar Creek Golf Course #18 green and the majestic mountain ranges beyond. With 5 bedrooms plus an office boasting a separate entrance, this residence offers both versatility and comfort. Nestled amidst pristine landscaping on an oversized lot, it's designed for both storage and entertaining, providing ample room to embrace the Wyoming lifestyle. Crafted with meticulous attention to detail, this home exudes sophistication with its hardwood floors, Indian slate accents, and cedar tongue-and-groove ceilings. Three cozy fireplaces add warmth and charm throughout, while modern conveniences such as surround sound, security system, and central vacuum enhance everyday living. The enchanting master suite beckons with a gas fireplace, dual sinks and closets, and a luxurious Jacuzzi, offering a tranquil retreat. Descend to the lower level, where entertainment awaits in the form of a well-appointed sports bar, complete with a kitchenette and wine storage, alongside a dedicated movie room a perfect space for hosting gatherings and creating lasting memories. And for ultimate relaxation, indulge in the second Jacuzzi, promising moments of rejuvenation amidst the serene surroundings.
